{{This date in recent years}}
{{Day}}

==Events==
* [[636]] &ndash; [[Arab–Byzantine wars]]: The [[Battle of Yarmouk]] between [[Byzantine Empire]] and [[Rashidun Caliphate]] begins.
* [[717]] &ndash; Arab–Byzantine wars: [[Maslamah ibn Abd al-Malik]] begins the [[Second Arab Siege of Constantinople]], which will last for nearly a year.
* [[718]] &ndash; Arab–Byzantine wars: Raising of the [[Siege of Constantinople (717–718)|Second Arab Siege of Constantinople]].
* [[778]] &ndash; The [[Battle of Roncevaux Pass (778)|Battle of Roncevaux Pass]], at which [[Roland]] is killed.
* [[927]] &ndash; The [[Saracen]]s conquer and destroy [[Taranto]].
* [[982]] &ndash; [[Holy Roman Emperor]] [[Otto II, Holy Roman Emperor|Otto II]] is defeated by the [[Saracens]] in the [[Battle of Capo Colonna]], in [[Calabria]]
*[[1018]] &ndash; Byzantine general [[Eustathios Daphnomeles]] blinds and captures [[Ivats|Ibatzes of Bulgaria]] by a ruse, thereby ending Bulgarian resistance against Emperor [[Basil II]]'s conquest of [[First Bulgarian Empire|Bulgaria]].
*[[1040]] &ndash; King [[Duncan I of Scotland|Duncan I]] is killed in battle against his first cousin and rival [[Macbeth, King of Scotland|Macbeth]]. The latter succeeds him as [[List of Scottish monarchs|King of Scotland]].
*[[1057]] &ndash; King Macbeth is killed at the [[Battle of Lumphanan]] by the forces of [[Malcolm III of Scotland|Máel Coluim mac Donnchada]].
*[[1070]] &ndash; The [[Pavia]]n-born [[Benedictine]] [[Lanfranc]] is appointed as the new [[Archbishop of Canterbury]] in [[Kingdom of England|England]].
*[[1185]] &ndash; The cave city of [[Vardzia]] is consecrated by Queen [[Tamar of Georgia]].
*[[1237]] &ndash; The [[Battle of the Puig]] takes place in the context of the [[Spanish Reconquista]] pitting the forces of the [[Taifa of Valencia]] against the [[Kingdom of Aragon]]. The battle resulted in an Aragonese victory.
*[[1248]] &ndash; The [[Cornerstone|foundation stone]] of [[Cologne Cathedral]], built to house the [[Shrine of the Three Kings|relics of the]] [[Biblical Magi|Three Wise Men]], is laid. (Construction is eventually completed in [[1880]].)
*[[1261]] &ndash; [[Michael VIII Palaiologos]] is crowned [[List of Byzantine emperors|Byzantine emperor]] in [[Constantinople]].
*[[1281]] &ndash; [[Mongol invasions of Japan|Mongol invasion of Japan]]: The [[Mongol Empire|Mongolian]] fleet of [[Kublai Khan]] is destroyed by a "[[kamikaze (typhoon)|divine wind]]" for the second time in the [[Battle of Kōan]].
*[[1309]] &ndash; [[Rhodes (city)|The city of Rhodes]] surrenders to the forces of the [[Knights Hospitaller|Knights of St. John]], completing their conquest of [[Rhodes]]. The knights establish their headquarters on the island and rename themselves the [[Knights Hospitaller|Knights of Rhodes]].
*[[1430]] &ndash; [[Francesco I Sforza|Francesco Sforza]], lord of [[Milan]], conquers [[Lucca]].
*[[1461]] &ndash; The [[Empire of Trebizond]] surrenders to the forces of Sultan [[Mehmed II]]. This is regarded by some historians as the real end of the [[Byzantine Empire]]. Emperor [[David of Trebizond|David]] is exiled and later murdered.
*[[1483]] &ndash; [[Pope Sixtus IV]] consecrates the [[Sistine Chapel]].
*[[1511]] &ndash; [[Afonso de Albuquerque]] of [[Portugal]] [[Capture of Malacca (1511)|conquers]] [[Malacca]], the capital of the [[Malacca Sultanate]].
*[[1517]] &ndash; Seven Portuguese armed [[Watercraft|vessels]] led by [[Fernão Pires de Andrade]] meet [[China|Chinese]] officials at the [[Pearl River Delta|Pearl River estuary]].
*[[1519]] &ndash; [[Panama City]], [[Panama]], is founded.
*[[1534]] &ndash; Saint [[Ignatius of Loyola]] and six classmates take initial vows, leading to the creation of the [[Society of Jesus]] in September 1540.
*[[1537]] &ndash; [[Asunción]], [[Paraguay]], is founded.
*[[1540]] &ndash; [[Arequipa]], [[Peru]], is founded.
*[[1549]] &ndash; [[Society of Jesus|Jesuit]] [[priest]] Saint [[Francis Xavier]] comes ashore at [[Kagoshima]] (Traditional [[Japanese calendar|Japanese date]]: July 22, 1549).
*[[1599]] &ndash; [[Nine Years' War (Ireland)|Nine Years' War]]: [[Battle of Curlew Pass]] – Irish forces led by [[Hugh Roe O'Donnell]] successfully ambush English forces, led by Sir [[Conyers Clifford]], sent to relieve Collooney Castle.
*[[1695]] &ndash; [[Early modern France|French]] forces end the [[Bombardment of Brussels]], leaving a third of the buildings in the city in ruins.
*[[1760]] &ndash; [[Seven Years' War]]: [[Battle of Liegnitz (1760)|Battle of Liegnitz]] – [[Frederick the Great]]'s victory over the [[Austrians]] under [[Ernst Gideon von Laudon]].
*[[1812]] &ndash; [[War of 1812]]: The [[Battle of Fort Dearborn]] is fought between [[United States]] troops and [[Potawatomi]] at what is now [[Chicago|Chicago, Illinois]].
*[[1843]] &ndash; The [[Cathedral of Our Lady of Peace]] in [[Honolulu|Honolulu, Hawaii]] is dedicated. Now the cathedral of the [[Roman Catholic Diocese of Honolulu]], it is the oldest [[Catholic Church|Roman Catholic]] [[cathedral]] in continuous use in the United States.
*  1843   &ndash; [[Tivoli Gardens]], one of the oldest still intact [[amusement park]]s in the world, opens in [[Copenhagen]], [[Denmark]].
*[[1863]] &ndash; The [[Bombardment of Kagoshima|Anglo-Satsuma War]] begins between the [[Satsuma Domain]] of [[Japan]] and the [[United Kingdom]] (Traditional [[Japanese calendar|Japanese date]]: July 2, 1863).
*[[1869]] &ndash; The [[Government of Meiji Japan|Meiji government]] in [[Japan]] establishes six new ministries, including one for [[Shinto]].
*[[1893]] &ndash; [[Ibadan]] area became a British [[Protectorate]] after a treaty signed by Fijabi, the [[Olubadan|Baale of Ibadan]] with the British acting Governor of [[Lagos Colony|Lagos]], George C. Denton.
*[[1907]] &ndash; Ordination in Constantinople of Fr. [[Raphael Morgan]], first African-American [[Eastern Orthodox Church|Orthodox]] priest, "Priest-Apostolic" to America and the West Indies.
*[[1914]] &ndash; A male servant of American [[architect]] [[Frank Lloyd Wright]] sets fire to the living quarters of the architect's [[Wisconsin]] home, [[Taliesin (studio)|Taliesin]], murders seven people and burns the living quarters to the ground.
*  1914   &ndash; The [[Panama Canal]] opens to traffic with the transit of the cargo ship {{SS|Ancon}}.
*  1914   &ndash; The [[1st Army (Russian Empire)|First Russian Army]], led by [[Paul von Rennenkampf]], enters [[East Prussia]].
*  1914   &ndash; The beginning of the [[Battle of Cer]].
*[[1915]] &ndash; A story in ''[[New York World]]'' [[Great Phenol Plot|reveals]] that the [[Weimar Republic|Weimar German government]] had purchased excess [[phenol]] from [[Thomas Edison]] that could be used to make explosives for the war effort and diverted it to [[Bayer]] for [[aspirin]] production.
*[[1920]] &ndash; [[Battle of Warsaw (1920)|Battle of Warsaw]] so called Miracle at the Vistula.
*[[1935]] &ndash; [[Will Rogers]] and [[Wiley Post]] are killed after their aircraft develops engine problems during takeoff in [[Barrow, Alaska]].
*[[1939]] &ndash; 13 [[Junkers Ju 87|Stukas]] dive into the ground during a disastrous air-practice at Neuhammer. There are no survivors.
*  1939   &ndash; ''[[The Wizard of Oz (1939 film)|The Wizard of Oz]]'' premiered at Grauman's Chinese Theater in [[Los Angeles|Los Angeles, California]].
*[[1940]] &ndash; An [[Italy|Italian]] submarine torpedoes and sinks the [[Greek cruiser Elli (1912)|Greek cruiser ''Elli'']] at [[Tinos]] harbor during peacetime, marking the most serious Italian provocation prior to the outbreak of the [[Greco-Italian War]] in October.
*[[1941]] &ndash; Corporal [[Josef Jakobs]] is executed by firing squad at the [[Tower of London]] at 7:12&nbsp;am, making him the last person to be executed at the Tower for [[espionage]].
*[[1942]] &ndash; [[World War II]]: [[Operation Pedestal]] – The {{SS|Ohio}} reaches the island of [[Malta]] barely afloat carrying vital fuel supplies for the island's defenses.
*[[1944]] &ndash; World War II: [[Operation Dragoon]] – Allied forces land in [[southern France]].
*[[1945]] &ndash; World War II: [[Surrender of Japan|Japan surrenders]] to end the war.
*[[1947]] &ndash; [[India]] gains [[Indian independence movement|Independence]] from the [[British Empire|British]] [[British Raj|Indian Empire]] and joins the [[Commonwealth of Nations]].
*  1947   &ndash; Founder of [[Pakistan]], [[Muhammad Ali Jinnah]] is sworn in as first [[Governor-General of Pakistan]] in [[Karachi]].
*[[1948]] &ndash; The [[South Korea|Republic of Korea]] is established south of the [[38th parallel north]].
*[[1952]] &ndash; [[Lynmouth Flood|A flash flood]] drenches the town of [[Lynmouth|Lynmouth, England]], United Kingdom, killing 34 people.
*[[1954]] &ndash; [[Alfredo Stroessner]] begins his dictatorship in Paraguay.
*[[1960]] &ndash; [[Republic of the Congo]] ([[Brazzaville]]) becomes independent from [[France]].
*[[1961]] &ndash; [[Conrad Schumann]] flees from [[East Germany]] while on duty guarding the construction of the [[Berlin Wall]].
*[[1962]] &ndash; [[James Joseph Dresnok]] defects to [[North Korea]] after running across the [[Korean Demilitarized Zone]]. Dresnok still resides in the capital, [[Pyongyang]].
*[[1963]] &ndash; Execution of [[Henry John Burnett]], the last man to be hanged in [[Scotland]], UK.
*  1963   &ndash; President [[Fulbert Youlou]] is overthrown in the [[Republic of the Congo]], after a [[Trois Glorieuses (1963)|three-day uprising]] in the capital.
*[[1965]] &ndash; [[The Beatles]] play to nearly [[The Beatles' 1965 US tour|60,000 fans at Shea Stadium]] in [[New York City|New York, New York]], an event later regarded as the birth of [[arena rock|stadium rock]].
*[[1969]] &ndash; [[Woodstock]] opens.
*[[1970]] &ndash; [[Patricia Palinkas]] became the first woman to play professionally in an [[American football]] game
*[[1971]] &ndash; [[President of the United States|President]] [[Richard Nixon]] completes the break from the [[gold standard]] by [[Nixon Shock|ending]] convertibility of the [[United States dollar]] into gold by foreign investors.
*  1971   &ndash; [[Bahrain]] gains [[Bahrain Independence Day|independence]] from the United Kingdom.
*[[1973]] &ndash; [[Vietnam War]]: The United States bombing of [[Cambodia]] ends.
*[[1974]] &ndash; [[Yuk Young-soo]], [[First Lady]] of [[South Korea]], is killed during an apparent assassination attempt upon [[President of South Korea]], [[Park Chung-hee]].
*[[1975]] &ndash; [[Bangladesh]]'s founder [[Sheikh Mujibur Rahman]] is killed along with most members of his family during a military coup.
*  1975   &ndash; [[Takeo Miki]] makes the first official pilgrimage to [[Yasukuni Shrine]] by an incumbent [[Prime Minister of Japan|prime minister]] on the anniversary of the end of World War II.
*[[1977]] &ndash; [[Ohio State University Radio Observatory|The Big Ear]], a [[radio telescope]] operated by [[Ohio State University]] as part of the [[Search for extraterrestrial intelligence|SETI]] project, receives a radio signal from deep space; the event is named the "[[Wow! signal]]" from the notation made by a volunteer on the project.
*[[1984]] &ndash; The [[Kurdistan Workers' Party|PKK]] in [[Turkey]] starts a campaign of armed attacks upon the Turkish military with an [[1984 PKK attacks|attack on police and gendarmerie bases in Şemdinli and Eruh]]
*[[1995]] &ndash; In [[South Carolina]], [[Shannon Faulkner]] becomes the first female [[cadet]] matriculated at [[The Citadel, The Military College of South Carolina|The Citadel]] (she drops out less than a week later).
*[[1996]] &ndash; [[President of Turkey]] [[Süleyman Demirel]] approved to "Law of ban For Casino in [[Turkey]]"
*[[1998]] &ndash; [[Omagh bombing]] in [[Northern Ireland]], the worst [[terrorism|terrorist]] incident of [[The Troubles]]
*[[1999]] &ndash; [[Béni Ounif|Beni Ounif massacre]] in [[Algeria]]; some 29 people are killed at a false roadblock near the Moroccan border, leading to temporary tensions with [[Morocco]].
*[[2005]] &ndash; [[Israel's unilateral disengagement plan]] to evict all [[Israelis]] from the [[Gaza Strip]] and from four [[Israeli settlement|settlements]] in the northern [[West Bank]] begins.
*[[2007]] &ndash; An [[2007 Peru earthquake|8.0-magnitude earthquake]] off the [[Pacific coast]] devastates [[Ica Region|Ica]] and various regions of [[Peru]] killing 514 and injuring 1,090.
*[[2013]] &ndash; At least 27 people are killed and 226 injured in an [[August 2013 Beirut bombing|explosion]] in southern [[Beirut]] near a complex used by Lebanon's militant group [[Hezbollah]] in Lebanon. A previously unknown [[Syria|Syrian]] [[Sunni]] group claims responsibility in an online video
*  2013   &ndash; The [[Smithsonian]] announces the discovery of the [[olinguito]], the first new carnivoran species found in the Americas in 35 years.

